Commentary : Two Decades of China 's Dynamic Diplomacy ( 2 )
Numerous other countries , especially developing countries , have praised China 's active participation in multilateral and international activities , as well as its efforts to uphold justice in world affairs and strict opposition to hegemonism and power politics .
China , a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council , has played a special and active role in promoting just and peaceful settlements of major regional conflicts .
China has ignored pressure and staunchly insisted on ensuring the stability of its yuan throughout the ongoing financial crisis engulfing Asia currencies .
Moreover , the 5.5 billion U.S. dollars in aid China has provided to relevant countries have helped prevent the crisis from worsening and have been the subject of high praise from the international community .
China has initiated dialogue and cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual respect , and opposes interference in the internal affairs of any country under the pretext of human rights .
China has successfully defeated seven anti-China motions a few western countries have tabled at human right conferences in Geneva .
In addition , China has actively participated in disarmament activities and talks on the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty .
China was in fact one of the first nations to sign the treaty .
